18// Evaluates x and returns false if false.
19#define RETURN_IF_FALSE(x) \
20 if (!(x)) { \
21 return false; \
22 }
23
24// Evaluates x, which is intended to return an optional. If result is nullopt,
25// returns false. Else, calls fun() with the dereferenced optional as parameter.
26#define READ_OR_RETURN(x, fun) \
27 do { \
28 if (auto optional_val = (x)) { \
29 fun(*optional_val); \
30 } else { \
31 return false; \
32 } \
33 } while (false)
34
35namespace vp9 {
36namespace {
37const size_t kVp9NumRefsPerFrame = 3;
38const size_t kVp9MaxRefLFDeltas = 4;
39const size_t kVp9MaxModeLFDeltas = 2;
40const size_t kVp9MinTileWidthB64 = 4;
41const size_t kVp9MaxTileWidthB64 = 64;
42
43class BitstreamReader {
44 public:
45 explicit BitstreamReader(rtc::BitBuffer* buffer) : buffer_(buffer) {}
46
47 // Reads on bit from the input stream and:
48 // * returns false if bit cannot be read
49 // * calls f_true() if bit is true, returns return value of that function
50 // * calls f_else() if bit is false, returns return value of that function
51 bool IfNextBoolean(
52 std::function<bool()> f_true,
53 std::function<bool()> f_false = [] { return true; }) {
54 uint32_t val;
55 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(1, val)) {
56 return false;
57 }
58 if (val != 0) {
59 return f_true();
60 }
61 return f_false();
62 }
63
64 absl::optional<bool> ReadBoolean() {
65 uint32_t val;
66 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(1, val)) {
67 return {};
68 }
69 return {val != 0};
70 }
71
72 // Reads a bit from the input stream and returns:
73 // * false if bit cannot be read
74 // * true if bit matches expected_val
75 // * false if bit does not match expected_val - in which case |error_msg| is
76 // logged as warning, if provided.
77 bool VerifyNextBooleanIs(bool expected_val, absl::string_view error_msg) {
78 uint32_t val;
79 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(1, val)) {
80 return false;
81 }
82 if ((val != 0) != expected_val) {
83 if (!error_msg.empty()) {
84 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << error_msg;
85 }
86 return false;
87 }
88 return true;
89 }
90
91 // Reads |bits| bits from the bitstream and interprets them as an unsigned
92 // integer that gets cast to the type T before returning.
93 // Returns nullopt if all bits cannot be read.
94 // If number of bits matches size of data type, the bits parameter may be
95 // omitted. Ex:
96 // ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(2); // Returns uint8_t with 2 LSB populated.
97 // ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(); // Returns uint8_t with all 8 bits populated.
98 template <typename T>
99 absl::optional<T> ReadUnsigned(int bits = sizeof(T) * 8) {
100 RTC_DCHECK_LE(bits, 32);
101 RTC_DCHECK_LE(bits, sizeof(T) * 8);
102 uint32_t val;
103 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(bits, val)) {
104 return {};
105 }
106 return (static_cast<T>(val));
107 }
108
109 // Helper method that reads |num_bits| from the bitstream, returns:
110 // * false if bits cannot be read.
111 // * true if |expected_val| matches the read bits
112 // * false if |expected_val| does not match the read bits, and logs
113 // |error_msg| as a warning (if provided).
114 bool VerifyNextUnsignedIs(int num_bits,
115 uint32_t expected_val,
116 absl::string_view error_msg) {
117 uint32_t val;
118 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(num_bits, val)) {
119 return false;
120 }
121 if (val != expected_val) {
122 if (!error_msg.empty()) {
123 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << error_msg;
124 }
125 return false;
126 }
127 return true;
128 }
129
130 // Basically the same as ReadUnsigned() - but for signed integers.
131 // Here |bits| indicates the size of the value - number of bits read from the
132 // bit buffer is one higher (the sign bit). This is made to matche the spec in
133 // which eg s(4) = f(1) sign-bit, plus an f(4).
134 template <typename T>
135 absl::optional<T> ReadSigned(int bits = sizeof(T) * 8) {
136 uint32_t sign;
137 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(1, sign)) {
138 return {};
139 }
140 uint32_t val;
141 if (!buffer_->ReadBits(bits, val)) {
142 return {};
143 }
144 int64_t sign_val = val;
145 if (sign != 0) {
146 sign_val = -sign_val;
147 }
148 return {static_cast<T>(sign_val)};
149 }
150
151 // Reads |bits| from the bitstream, disregarding their value.
152 // Returns true if full number of bits were read, false otherwise.
153 bool ConsumeBits(int bits) { return buffer_->ConsumeBits(bits); }
154
155 private:
156 rtc::BitBuffer* buffer_;
157};
158
159bool Vp9ReadColorConfig(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
160 if (frame_info->profile == 2 || frame_info->profile == 3) {
161 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool ten_or_twelve_bits) {
162 frame_info->bit_detph =
163 ten_or_twelve_bits ? BitDept::k12Bit : BitDept::k10Bit;
164 });
165 } else {
166 frame_info->bit_detph = BitDept::k8Bit;
167 }
168
169 READ_OR_RETURN(
170 br->ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(3), [frame_info](uint8_t color_space) {
171 frame_info->color_space = static_cast<ColorSpace>(color_space);
172 });
173
174 if (frame_info->color_space != ColorSpace::CS_RGB) {
175 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool color_range) {
176 frame_info->color_range =
177 color_range ? ColorRange::kFull : ColorRange::kStudio;
178 });
179
180 if (frame_info->profile == 1 || frame_info->profile == 3) {
181 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(2),
182 [frame_info](uint8_t subsampling) {
183 switch (subsampling) {
184 case 0b00:
185 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k444;
186 break;
187 case 0b01:
188 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k440;
189 break;
190 case 0b10:
191 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k422;
192 break;
193 case 0b11:
194 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k420;
195 break;
196 }
197 });
198
199 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->VerifyNextBooleanIs(
200 0, "Failed to parse header. Reserved bit set."));
201 } else {
202 // Profile 0 or 2.
203 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k420;
204 }
205 } else {
206 // SRGB
207 frame_info->color_range = ColorRange::kFull;
208 if (frame_info->profile == 1 || frame_info->profile == 3) {
209 frame_info->sub_sampling = YuvSubsampling::k444;
210 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->VerifyNextBooleanIs(
211 0, "Failed to parse header. Reserved bit set."));
212 } else {
213 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse header. 4:4:4 color not supported"
214 " in profile 0 or 2.";
215 return false;
216 }
217 }
218
219 return true;
220}
221
222bool Vp9ReadFrameSize(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
223 // 16 bits: frame (width|height) - 1.
224 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint16_t>(), [frame_info](uint16_t width) {
225 frame_info->frame_width = width + 1;
226 });
227 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint16_t>(), [frame_info](uint16_t height) {
228 frame_info->frame_height = height + 1;
229 });
230 return true;
231}
232
233bool Vp9ReadRenderSize(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
234 // render_and_frame_size_different
235 return br->IfNextBoolean(
236 [&] {
237 // 16 bits: render (width|height) - 1.
238 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint16_t>(),
239 [frame_info](uint16_t width) {
240 frame_info->render_width = width + 1;
241 });
242 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint16_t>(),
243 [frame_info](uint16_t height) {
244 frame_info->render_height = height + 1;
245 });
246 return true;
247 },
248 /*else*/
249 [&] {
250 frame_info->render_height = frame_info->frame_height;
251 frame_info->render_width = frame_info->frame_width;
252 return true;
253 });
254}
255
256bool Vp9ReadFrameSizeFromRefs(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
257 bool found_ref = false;
258 for (size_t i = 0; !found_ref && i < kVp9NumRefsPerFrame; i++) {
259 // Size in refs.
260 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadBoolean(), [&](bool ref) { found_ref = ref; });
261 }
262
263 if (!found_ref) {
264 if (!Vp9ReadFrameSize(br, frame_info)) {
265 return false;
266 }
267 }
268 return Vp9ReadRenderSize(br, frame_info);
269}
270
271bool Vp9ReadLoopfilter(BitstreamReader* br) {
272 // 6 bits: filter level.
273 // 3 bits: sharpness level.
274 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->ConsumeBits(9));
275
276 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // if mode_ref_delta_enabled
277 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // if mode_ref_delta_update
278 for (size_t i = 0; i < kVp9MaxRefLFDeltas; i++) {
279 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean([&] { return br->ConsumeBits(7); }));
280 }
281 for (size_t i = 0; i < kVp9MaxModeLFDeltas; i++) {
282 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean([&] { return br->ConsumeBits(7); }));
283 }
284 return true;
285 });
286 });
287}
288
289bool Vp9ReadQp(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
290 READ_OR_RETURN(br->ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(),
291 [frame_info](uint8_t qp) { frame_info->base_qp = qp; });
292
293 // yuv offsets
294 for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
295 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean([br] { // if delta_coded
296 return br->ConsumeBits(5);
297 }));
298 }
299 return true;
300}
301
302bool Vp9ReadSegmentationParams(BitstreamReader* br) {
303 constexpr int kVp9MaxSegments = 8;
304 constexpr int kVp9SegLvlMax = 4;
305 constexpr int kSegmentationFeatureBits[kVp9SegLvlMax] = {8, 6, 2, 0};
306 constexpr bool kSegmentationFeatureSigned[kVp9SegLvlMax] = {1, 1, 0, 0};
307
308 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // segmentation_enabled
309 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // update_map
310 // Consume probs.
311 for (int i = 0; i < 7; ++i) {
312 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean([br] { return br->ConsumeBits(7); }));
313 }
314
315 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // temporal_update
316 // Consume probs.
317 for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
318 RETURN_IF_FALSE(
319 br->IfNextBoolean([br] { return br->ConsumeBits(7); }));
320 }
321 return true;
322 });
323 });
324 });
325
326 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] {
327 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->ConsumeBits(1)); // abs_or_delta
328 for (int i = 0; i < kVp9MaxSegments; ++i) {
329 for (int j = 0; j < kVp9SegLvlMax; ++j) {
330 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean([&] { // feature_enabled
331 return br->ConsumeBits(kSegmentationFeatureBits[j] +
332 kSegmentationFeatureSigned[j]);
333 }));
334 }
335 }
336 return true;
337 });
338}
339
340bool Vp9ReadTileInfo(BitstreamReader* br, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
341 size_t mi_cols = (frame_info->frame_width + 7) >> 3;
342 size_t sb64_cols = (mi_cols + 7) >> 3;
343
344 size_t min_log2 = 0;
345 while ((kVp9MaxTileWidthB64 << min_log2) < sb64_cols) {
346 ++min_log2;
347 }
348
349 size_t max_log2 = 1;
350 while ((sb64_cols >> max_log2) >= kVp9MinTileWidthB64) {
351 ++max_log2;
352 }
353 --max_log2;
354
355 size_t cols_log2 = min_log2;
356 bool done = false;
357 while (!done && cols_log2 < max_log2) {
358 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br->IfNextBoolean(
359 [&] {
360 ++cols_log2;
361 return true;
362 },
363 [&] {
364 done = true;
365 return true;
366 }));
367 }
368
369 // rows_log2;
370 return br->IfNextBoolean([&] { return br->ConsumeBits(1); });
371}
372} // namespace
373
374bool Parse(const uint8_t* buf, size_t length, FrameInfo* frame_info) {
375 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(buf, length);
376 BitstreamReader br(&bit_buffer);
377
378 // Frame marker.
379 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.VerifyNextUnsignedIs(
380 2, 0x2, "Failed to parse header. Frame marker should be 2."));
381
382 // Profile has low bit first.
383 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(),
384 [frame_info](bool low) { frame_info->profile = int{low}; });
385 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool high) {
386 frame_info->profile |= int{high} << 1;
387 });
388 if (frame_info->profile > 2) {
389 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.VerifyNextBooleanIs(
390 false, "Failed to get QP. Unsupported bitstream profile."));
391 }
392
393 // Show existing frame.
394 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.IfNextBoolean([&] {
395 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadUnsigned<uint8_t>(3),
396 [frame_info](uint8_t frame_idx) {
397 frame_info->show_existing_frame = frame_idx;
398 });
399 return true;
400 }));
401 if (frame_info->show_existing_frame.has_value()) {
402 return true;
403 }
404
405 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool frame_type) {
406 // Frame type: KEY_FRAME(0), INTER_FRAME(1).
407 frame_info->is_keyframe = frame_type == 0;
408 });
409 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool show_frame) {
410 frame_info->show_frame = show_frame;
411 });
412 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(), [frame_info](bool error_resilient) {
413 frame_info->error_resilient = error_resilient;
414 });
415
416 if (frame_info->is_keyframe) {
417 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.VerifyNextUnsignedIs(
418 24, 0x498342, "Failed to get QP. Invalid sync code."));
419
420 if (!Vp9ReadColorConfig(&br, frame_info))
421 return false;
422 if (!Vp9ReadFrameSize(&br, frame_info))
423 return false;
424 if (!Vp9ReadRenderSize(&br, frame_info))
425 return false;
426 } else {
427 // Non-keyframe.
428 bool is_intra_only = false;
429 if (!frame_info->show_frame) {
430 READ_OR_RETURN(br.ReadBoolean(),
431 [&](bool intra_only) { is_intra_only = intra_only; });
432 }
433 if (!frame_info->error_resilient) {
434 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(2)); // Reset frame context.
435 }
436
437 if (is_intra_only) {
438 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.VerifyNextUnsignedIs(
439 24, 0x498342, "Failed to get QP. Invalid sync code."));
440
441 if (frame_info->profile > 0) {
442 if (!Vp9ReadColorConfig(&br, frame_info))
443 return false;
444 }
445 // Refresh frame flags.
446 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(8));
447 if (!Vp9ReadFrameSize(&br, frame_info))
448 return false;
449 if (!Vp9ReadRenderSize(&br, frame_info))
450 return false;
451 } else {
452 // Refresh frame flags.
453 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(8));
454
455 for (size_t i = 0; i < kVp9NumRefsPerFrame; i++) {
456 // 3 bits: Ref frame index.
457 // 1 bit: Ref frame sign biases.
458 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(4));
459 }
460
461 if (!Vp9ReadFrameSizeFromRefs(&br, frame_info))
462 return false;
463
464 // Allow high precision mv.
465 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(1));
466 // Interpolation filter.
467 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.IfNextBoolean([] { return true; },
468 [&br] { return br.ConsumeBits(2); }));
469 }
470 }
471
472 if (!frame_info->error_resilient) {
473 // 1 bit: Refresh frame context.
474 // 1 bit: Frame parallel decoding mode.
475 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(2));
476 }
477
478 // Frame context index.
479 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(2));
480
481 if (!Vp9ReadLoopfilter(&br))
482 return false;
483
484 // Read base QP.
485 RETURN_IF_FALSE(Vp9ReadQp(&br, frame_info));
486
487 const bool kParseFullHeader = false;
488 if (kParseFullHeader) {
489 // Currently not used, but will be needed when parsing beyond the
490 // uncompressed header.
491 RETURN_IF_FALSE(Vp9ReadSegmentationParams(&br));
492
493 RETURN_IF_FALSE(Vp9ReadTileInfo(&br, frame_info));
494
495 RETURN_IF_FALSE(br.ConsumeBits(16)); // header_size_in_bytes
496 }
497
498 return true;
499}
500
501bool GetQp(const uint8_t* buf, size_t length, int* qp) {
502 FrameInfo frame_info;
503 if (!Parse(buf, length, &frame_info)) {
504 return false;
505 }
506 *qp = frame_info.base_qp;
507 return true;
508}
509
510absl::optional<FrameInfo> ParseIntraFrameInfo(const uint8_t* buf,
511 size_t length) {
512 FrameInfo frame_info;
513 if (Parse(buf, length, &frame_info) && frame_info.frame_width > 0) {
514 return frame_info;
515 }
516 return absl::nullopt;
517}
